{"nodes": [{"id": "draft6_0_src_phase9_readme", "label": "Phase 9 \u2014 README (freeze the maintenance loop)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft6.0/src/phase9/README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_phase9_readme_s13_eviction", "label": "CBRS committed as bounded-LUT eviction (S13)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0/src/phase9/README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "At a pinned pressure-point cap where the bound bites hard, class-balanced reservoir sampling (CBRS) is the best-bounded eviction policy \u2014 it ties a herding null (density\u2248class at this buffer, a buffer-spine null) and decisively beats reservoir/recency (\u22120.400 vs \u22120.607/\u22120.707) because it keeps prototypes balanced across classes, spanning the class directions even at a tight budget. The minimum holding cap grows with class count \u2014 a scaling-law flag."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_phase9_readme_proto_reanchor", "label": "proto-reanchor \u2014 the earned read-side defense", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0/src/phase9/README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Re-forwards the raw LUT prototypes through the current SCFF bulk under the same device offset, producing drift-free, shift-consistent prototypes; recovers the Phase-6 input-transducer directional residual's retention from 0.787 to 0.986, discharging the 'scoped-YES \u2192 Stage-2 read-side' debt using the plan's own sleep mechanism \u2014 direction-grounded, never an entropy/confidence magnitude."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_phase9_readme_grid4_refreeze", "label": "grid-4 \u2014 the re-confirmed lifelong sleep cadence", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0/src/phase9/README.md", "source_location": null, 